Reasoning: The paper deals with Counting Monadic Second Order (CMSO) sentences and their solvability on graphs, which falls under the category of logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the design of parameterized algorithms, which suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding a connected induced subgraph with a CMSO-definable property relates to graph theory (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
